@@TJvID3Controller.FindNextFrame
Summary
  Returns the next frame in the tag with a specific frame identifier.
Description
  Call FindNextFrame to search for the first frame found after the frame specified by From, with
  AFrameID as frame identifier in the tag.

  Example, search for a picture frame with a specific picture type:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  function FindPictureType(const APictureType: TJvID3PictureType): TJvID3PictureFrame; var
    Frame: TJvID3Frame;
  begin
    Result := nil;

    if not JvID3v21.FindFirstFrame(fiPicture, Frame) then
      Exit;

    while (Frame is TJvID3PictureFrame) and
          (TJvID3PictureFrame(Frame).PictureType <> AType) do
      JvID3v21.FindNextFrame(fiPicture, Frame);

    if Frame is TJvID3PictureFrame then
      Result := TJvID3PictureFrame(Frame);
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
Parameters
  AFrameID - The frame identifier to search for.
  From     - Specifies the frame after which to search for the frame identifier. FindNextFrame sets
              From to the next frame found or nil if no such frame was found.
Return value
  Returns true when a frame was found, or false otherwise.
See Also
  <LINK FindFirstFrame>

