@@TJvID3FileInfo
Summary
  Contains information about a MP3 file.
Description
  The TJvID3FileInfo object contains information about a MP3 file, as found in the MPEG Audio
  Frame Header, and in the Xing or extended Info tag if those exists.

  This information indicates how the MP3 file is encoded.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Bitrate
Summary
  Indicates the bitrate of the MP3 file in kbit/s.
Description
  Read Bitrate to determine the bitrate of the MP3 file.
Note
  MPEG files may have variable bitrate (VBR). This means that bitrate in the file may change per
  frame. If so, then Bitrate indicates the average bitrate in the file.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.IsVBR

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Bits
Summary
  Specifies MPEG characteristics for an audio file.
Description
  Read Bits to determine some MPEG characteristics for an audio file.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.ChannelMode
Summary
  Specifies the channel mode of the MP3 file.
Description
  Read ChannelMode to determine the channel mode for an audio file.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Emphasis
Summary
  Specifies the emphasis of the MP3 file.
Description
  The emphasis tells the decoder that the file must be de-emphasized, i.e.,
  the decoder must 're-equalize' the sound after a Dolby-like noise supression. It is rarely used.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.FileSize
Summary
  Indicates the size of the MP3 file in bytes.
Description
  Read FileSize to determine the size of the MP3 file in bytes.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.HeaderFoundAt, TJvID3FileInfo.LengthInSec

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.FrameCount
Summary
  Indicates the number of MPEG frames in the MP3 file.
Description
  Read FrameCount to determine the number of MPEG frames in the MP3 file. If no Xing or Info tag is
  found, the value is an approximation.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.FrameLengthInBytes

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.FrameLengthInBytes
Summary
  Indicates the length of a MPEG frame in the MP3 file.
Description
  Read FrameLengthInBytes to determine the length of a MPEG frame in the MP3 file. If no Xing or Info
  tag is found, the value is an approximation.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.FrameCount

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.HeaderFoundAt
Summary
  Indicates the location in the MP3 file where at the MPEG header is found.
Description
  Read HeaderFoundAt to determine the location in the MP3 file where the MPEG Audio
  Frame Header was found. If HeaderFoundAt is smaller than 0, then no MPEG header was found.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.IsValid

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.IsValid
Summary
  Indicates whether a valid MPEG header is found in the MP3 file.
Description
  Read IsValid to determine whether the information provided by the properties of the file info
  object are valid.

  IsValid is true if a valid MPEG header is found in the MP3 file. If so, then HeaderFoundAt
  indicates the position in the file where the MPEG header tag was found.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.HeaderFoundAt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.IsVBR
Summary
  Indicates whether the MP3 file has a variable bitrate (VBR).
Description
  MPEG files may have variable bitrate (VBR). This means that bitrate in the file may change per
  frame. If IsVbr is true then property Bitrate indicates the average bitrate in the file.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.Bitrate

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Layer
Summary
  Indicates the layer of the MP3 file.
Description
  Read Layer to determine the layer of the MP3 file.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.Version

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.LengthInSec
Summary
  Indicates the length in seconds of the MP3 file.
Description
  Read LengthInSec to determine the length in seconds of the MP3 file.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.FileSize

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.ModeExtension
Summary
  Indicates the mode extension of the MP3 file.
Description
  Read ModeExtension to determine the mode extension of the MP3 file.

  Mode extension is used to join informations that are of no use for stereo effect, thus reducing
  needed bits. These bits are dynamically determined by an encoder in Joint stereo mode, and Joint
  Stereo can be changed from one frame to another, or even switched on or off.

  Complete frequency range of MPEG file is divided in subbands. There are 32 subbands.
  For Layer I & II, ModeExtension determines frequency range (bands) where intensity stereo is
  applied.
  For Layer III, ModeExtension determines which type of joint stereo is used (intensity stereo or m/s
  stereo). Frequency range is determined within decompression algorithm.

  Layer I & II:
  <TABLE>
  Value         Frequency range
  -------       ---------------
  meModeExt0    bands 4 to 31
  meModeExt1    bands 8 to 31
  meModeExt2    bands 12 to 31
  meModeExt3    bands 16 to 31
  </TABLE>

  Layer III:
  <TABLE>
  Value         \Intensity stereo    MS stereo
  -------       ----------------     ---------
  meModeExt0    off                  off
  meModeExt1    on                   off
  meModeExt2    off                  on
  meModeExt3    on                   on
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Read
Summary
  Reads file information from a specific stream.
Description
  Call Read to read file information from the stream specified by parameter AStream.
Parameters
  AStream - The stream wherefore to determine the file information.
  Offset  - The starting point in the stream.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.SamplingRateFrequency
Summary
  Indicates the sampling rate frequency of the MP3 file in Hz.
Description
  Read SamplingRateFrequency to determine the sampling rate frequency of the MP3 file in Hz, as found
  in the MPEG header tag.

  Possible values are:

  * For MPEG version 1: 32000, 44100 or 48000 Hz.
  * For MPEG version 2: 16000, 22050 or 24000 Hz.
  * For MPEG version 2.5: 8000, 11025 or 12000 Hz.
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.Version

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FileInfo.Version
Summary
  Indicates the MPEG version of the MP3 file.
Description
  Read Version to determine the MPEG version of the MP3 file, as found in the MPEG header tag.
  <TABLE>
  Value         Meaning
  -----         -------
  mvVersion1    MPEG Version 1 (ISO/IEC 11172-3)
  mvVersion2    MPEG Version 2 (ISO/IEC 13818-3)
  mvVersion25   MPEG Version 2.5
  mvReserved    An undefined MPEG version
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvID3FileInfo.Layer

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame
Summary
  Common ancestor of all the frame components.
Description
  TJvID3Frame encapsulates the fundamental behavior common to all frame components. It introduces the
  properties, events, and methods that are used to:

  * Change the encoding of a frame.
  * Convert the frame by changing the frame identifier.
  * \Check the values of the frame.
  * Determine whether a specific frame can be added to the tag.

  Do not create instances of TJvID3Frame. TJvID3Frame descendants are created automatically each time
  a tag controller is activated.

  A frame in a tag is always treated as one of the following TJvID3Frame descendant classes below:

  <TABLE>
  TJvID3AudioEncryptionFrame                 TJvID3PopularimeterFrame
  TJvID3BinaryFrame                          TJvID3SimpleListFrame
  TJvID3ContentFrame                         TJvID3SkipFrame
  TJvID3DoubleListFrame                      TJvID3TermsOfUseFrame
  TJvID3GeneralObjFrame                      TJvID3TextFrame
  TJvID3NumberFrame                          TJvID3TimestampFrame
  TJvID3OwnershipFrame                       TJvID3URLFrame
  TJvID3PictureFrame                         TJvID3URLUserFrame
  TJvID3PlayCounterFrame                     TJvID3UserFrame
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.CanAddFrame
Summary
  Returns whether a frame with a specific frame identifier can be added to the tag.
Description
  Call CanAddFrame to check whether a frame with a frame identifier as specified by parameter AFrameID
  can be added to the tag controlled by the tag controller.

  Certain frames may only appear once in a tag regardless of its value. For example, there may only
  be one fiAlbum frame in a tag.
Parameters
  AController - The tag controller that holds an ID3 v2 tag where to add the frame.
  AFrameID    - The frame identifier of the frame.
Return value
  Returns true if a frame with a frame identifier as specified by AFrameID can be added to the tag.
  Returns false otherwise.
See Also
  TJvID3Controller.Frames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.CheckFrame
Summary
  Indicates whether the value(s) of the frame are valid.
Description
  CheckFrame is used by a tag controller, to check whether the value(s) of the frames in the tag are
  valid.

  When HandleError is set to heAutoCorrect, then CheckFrame will auto correct invalid frames.
Parameters
  HandleError - Specifies how to handle errors.
Return value
  The return value of CheckFrame depends on the value of HandleError:
  <TABLE>
  HandleError           Return value
  -----------           ------------
  heAutoCorrect         Always returns true.
  heRaise               Raises an error when the frame is invalid, otherwise returns true.
  heBoolean             Returns false when the frame is invalid, otherwise returns true.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.ChangeToVersion

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Clear
Summary
  Clears the values of the frame.
Description
  Call the Clear method to give the frame a blank value.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.IsEmpty

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Controller
Summary
  Identifies the tag controller to which a frame belongs.
Description
  \Check the value of Controller to determine the tag controller that uses the frame component to
  represent one of the ID3 frames from the tag it controls. Applications should not directly assign
  the Controller property of a frame. It is assigned automatically when the frame is created, by
  calling AddFrame.
See Also
  TJvID3Controller.AddFrame

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Encoding
Summary
  Specifies the encoding for the frame.
Description
  Use Encoding to specify an encoding for the frame. Possible encodings are:

   * ISO-8859-1.
   * UTF-16 encoded Unicode with BOM.
   * UTF-16BE encoded Unicode without BOM. (only for version 2.4)
   * UTF-8 encoded Unicode. (only for version 2.4)

  Some frames allow different types of text encoding for specific fields of the frame (such as the
  <LINK TJvID3TextFrame.Text,text> field of TJvID3TextFrame);
  other fields are always represented as ISO-8859-1 characters (such as TJvID3PictureFrame.MIMEType).

  Property Encoding specifies the encoding of <i>all</i> fields that allow different types of text
  encoding of a frame. Frames that do not have fields that allow different types of text encoding,
  ignore the value of Encoding.

  Fields that allow different types of text encoding are typically accessable via two properties.
  One that has the name of the field as name, and can be used to access the ISO-8859-1 encoding of
  the field.
  The other has the name of the field postfixed with 'W' as name, and can be used to access the
  unicode encoding of the field. Examples are <LINK TJvID3PictureFrame.Description,Description> and
  <LINK TJvID3PictureFrame.DescriptionW,DescriptionW>, <LINK TJvID3GeneralObjFrame.FileName,FileName>
  and <LINK TJvID3GeneralObjFrame.FileNameW,FileNameW> etc.

  You can use the <LINK TJvID3Controller.ReadEncodingAs,ReadEncodingAs> property of a tag controller
  to specify the encoding of <i>all</i> frames after a tag has been read. Use the <LINK
  TJvID3Controller.WriteEncodingAs,WriteEncodingAs> property to specify with which encoding
  <i>all</i> frames are written to a tag.
See Also
  TJvID3Controller.ReadEncodingAs, TJvID3Controller.WriteEncodingAs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.EncryptionID
Summary
  Specifies with which method the frame is encrypted.
Description
  Use the EncryptionID to specify with which method the frame is encrypted. <b>Encryption is not
  supported by TJvID3Controller.</b>
Note
  EncryptionID is only valid if fhfIsEncrypted is included in Flags.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.Flags

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Flags
Summary
  Specifies 'status messages' and format description for the frame.
Description
  Use Flags to specify 'status messages' and format description for the frame. Use Flags to specify

  * whether to apply unsynchronization to this frame.
  * whether the contents of this frame are intended to be read only.
  * what the tag parser should do when it doesn't know the frame.

  Some properties are only valid if some flags are included in Flags:

  * EncryptionID is only valid if fhfIsEncrypted is included in Flags.
  * GroupID is only valid if fhfContainsGroupInformation is included in Flags.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.FrameID
Summary
  Specifies the frame identifier for the frame.
Description
  The tag controller uses the TJvID3FrameID type to identify frames. In the tag itself the frames are
  identified by a 4 character long name. FrameID identifies the frame by the TJvID3FrameID type and
  FrameName identifies the frame by the 4 characters.

  Read or set FrameID to determine or specify the frame identifier for the frame. When setting
  FrameID be sure that the frame identifier is supported by that specific TJvID3Frame descendant
  class.

  \Example:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  var
    TextFrame: TJvID3TextFrame;
  begin
    TextFrame := TJvID3TextFrame.FindOrCreate(MyController, fiAlbum);

    { TJvID3TextFrame supports fiTitleSortOrder }
    TextFrame.FrameID := fiTitleSortOrder;

    { TJvID3TextFrame does <i>not</i> support fiComment, thus this will
      generate an error }
    TextFrame.FrameID := fiComment;
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.FrameName

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.FrameName
Summary
  Specifies the tag frame identifier for the frame.
Description
  The tag controller uses the TJvID3FrameID type to identify frames. In the tag itself the frames are
  identified by a 4 character long name. FrameID identifies the frame by the TJvID3FrameID type and
  FrameName identifies the frame by the 4 characters.

  Read or set FrameName to determine or specify the frame identifier for the frame. When setting
  FrameName be sure that the frame identifier is supported by that specific TJvID3Frame descendant
  class.

  \Example:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  var
    TextFrame: TJvID3TextFrame;
  begin
    TextFrame := TJvID3TextFrame.FindOrCreate(MyController, fiAlbum);

    { TJvID3TextFrame supports fiTitleSortOrder (TSOT) }
    TextFrame.FrameName := 'TSOT';

    { TJvID3TextFrame does <i>not</i> support fiComment (COMM), thus this will
      generate an error }
    TextFrame.FrameName := 'COMM';
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.FrameID

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.FrameSize
Summary
  Indicates the amount of memory needed to store a frame.
Description
  \Check FrameSize to determine the number of bytes required to store a frame.

  The value of FrameSize for TJvID3Frame is 0. Most descendants of TJvID3Frame override this property
  to specify the size required by the specific frame they represent.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.GroupID
Summary
  Specifies the group identifier for this frame.
Description
  Property GroupID can be used to group specific frames. Every frame with the same group identifier
  belongs to the same group.
Note
  GroupID is only valid if fhfContainsGroupInformation is included in Flags.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.Flags

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Index
Summary
  Specifies the frame component’s index in the <LINK TJvID3Controller.Frames,Frames> property of the
  tag controller.
Description
  Use the Index property to:

  * Find the position of the frame in the tag.
  * Change the order of a frame's position in the tag by changing the value of Index. Changing   the
    Index value affects the position of the frames in the ID3 v2 tag.
Note
  The frame order can also be changed by dragging and dropping frames in the \Frames editor at design
  time.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.Frames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.IsEmpty
Summary
  Indicates whether the frame is empty.
Description
  Read IsEmpty to determine whether the frame is empty.

  The tag controller uses this property when coRemoveEmptyFrames is included in <LINK
  TJvID3Controller.Options,Options> to determine whether a frame can
  be removed from the tag.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.Clear

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frame.Stream
Summary
  Gives access to the tag stream.
Description
  Application should not use Stream. It's used by frames to write or read the frame data to the tag
  stream.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3FrameClass
<TITLE TJvID3FrameClass type>
Summary
  Defines the metaclass for TJvID3Frame.
Description
  TJvID3FrameClass is the metaclass for TJvID3Frame. Its value is the class reference for
  TJvID3Frame or for one of its descendants.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames
Summary
  Holds the frame (TJvID3Frame) objects that represent the frames in an ID3 v2 tag.
Description
  TJvID3Frames is used by a tag controller to manage the frame objects that correspond to frames in
  the tag.

  Use the properties and methods of TJvID3Frames to:

  * Access a specific frame.
  * Add or delete frames from the ID3 v2 tag.
  * Find out how many frames there are.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.Add
Summary
  Inserts a new frame to the end of the Frames array.
Description
  Applications do not normally call the Add method directly. When frame objects are created, Add is
  called automatically by the tag controller.

  Certain frames may only appear once in a tag regardless of its value. For example, there may only
  be one fiAlbum frame in a tag. Therefore use FindOrCreate to add frames to the tag, which checks
  whether there already exists such frame in the tag. For example:

 
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  var
    TextFrame: TJvTextFrame;
    PictureFrame: TJvPictureFrame;
  begin
    TextFrame := TJvTextFrame.FindOrCreate(MyTagController, fiAlbum);
    TextFrame.Text := 'Some album';

    PictureFrame := TJvPictureFrame.FindOrCreate(MyTagController, ptBand);
    PictureFrame.MIMEType := 'image/jpeg';
    PictureFrame.LoadFromFile('somepicture.jpg');
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
Parameters
  Frame - Specifies the frame to add.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.ChangeToVersion
Summary
  Changes all frames to a specific version.
Description
  ChangeToVersion is intended primarily for internal use. Use TJvID3Controller.Version instead.
Parameters
  ANewVersion - The new version for the frames.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.CheckFrames
Summary
  Indicates whether the value(s) of all frames are valid, and whether each frame is unique in the tag.
Description
  CheckFrame is used by a tag controller, to check whether the value(s) of the frames in the tag are
  valid.

  CheckFrame check for each frame in the tag, whether its values are correct. For example specifying
  an invalid language such as 'AAA' for the language property of a picture frame is incorrect.
  CheckFrame also checks whether all frames are unique in the tag. See CheckIsUnique for more info.

  When HandleError is set to heAutoCorrect, then CheckFrame will auto correct invalid frames,
  duplicate frames will then be removed of the tag.

  When you call <LINK TJvID3Controller.Commit,Commit> the tag controller always checks the value(s)
  of all frames are valid, and whether all frames in the tag are unique.
Parameters
  HandleError - Specifies how to handle errors.
Return value
  The return value of CheckFrame depends on the value of HandleError:
  <TABLE>
  HandleError           Return value
  -----------           ------------
  heAutoCorrect         Always returns true.
  heRaise               Raises an error when a frame is invalid, otherwise returns true.
  heBoolean             Returns false when a frame is invalid, otherwise returns true.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.ChangeToVersion

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.CheckIsUnique
Summary
  Checks whether a specific frame is unique in the tag.
Description
  Call CheckIsUnique to check whether a specific frame is unique in the tag.
  The ID3 v2 specification forbids that there are duplicate frames in the tag. What makes a frame a
  duplicate of another frame depends on the frame identifier, for example:

  * A <LINK TJvID3CustomTextFrame,text frame> is a duplicate of another text frame if it has the same
    frame identifier. For example, there may be only one fiAlbum frame in a tag.
  * A <LINK TJvID3ContentFrame,content frame> is a duplicate of another content frame if it has the
    same <LINK TJvID3ContentFrame.Language,language> and <LINK TJvID3ContentFrame.Description,
    content descriptor>.
  * A <LINK TJvID3PictureFrame,picture frame> is a duplicate of another picture frame if it has the
    same content descriptor (<LINK TJvID3PictureFrame.PictureType,PictureType> and
    <LINK TJvID3PictureFrame.Description,Description>) or both
    <LINK TJvID3PictureFrame.PictureType,PictureType> properties are set to ptOther or ptFileIcon.

  When you call <LINK TJvID3Controller.Commit,Commit> the tag controller always checks whether all
  frames in the tag are unique.
Parameters
  Frame - The frame to check.
Return value
  Returns true if no duplicate frame of the specific frame was found in the tag; returns false
  otherwise.
See Also
  TJvID3Controller.Commit, TJvID3Frames.CheckFrames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.Clear
Summary
  Deletes all frames from the TJvID3Frames object.
Description
  Clear empties the Frames property array.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.Frames, TJvID3Frames.RemoveEmptyFrames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.Count
Summary
  Indicates the number of frames in the frames object.
Description
  Use Count to determine the number of frames referenced by the TJvID3Frames object.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.Frames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.FindFrame@string
Summary
  Returns a frame given its frame name.
Description
  Call FindFrame to determine if a specified frame component is referenced in the TJvID3Frames object.

  The tag controller uses the TJvID3FrameID type to identify frames. In the tag itself the frames are
  identified by a 4 character long name. FrameID identifies the frame by the TJvID3FrameID type and
  FrameName identifies the frame by the 4 characters.
Note
  FindFrame differs from the FrameByName method only when the named frame is not in the list. When
  the frame is not found, FindFrame returns nil, while FrameByName raises an exception.
Parameters
  FrameID   - The frame identifier of the frame for which to search.
  FrameName - The frame name of the frame for which to search.
Return value
  If FindFrame finds a frame with a matching name,
  it returns the TJvID3Frame component for the specified frame. Otherwise it returns nil.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.FrameName, TJvID3Frames.FrameByID, TJvID3Frames.FrameByName

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.FindFrame@TJvID3FrameID
<COMBINE TJvID3Frames.FindFrame@string>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.FrameByID
Summary
  Returns a frame given its frame identifier.
Description
  Call FrameByID to determine if a specified frame component is referenced in the TJvID3Frames object.

  The tag controller uses the TJvID3FrameID type to identify frames. In the tag itself the frames are
  identified by a 4 character long name. Parameter FrameID identifies the frame by the
  TJvID3FrameID type.
Parameters
  FrameID   - The frame identifier of the frame for which to search.
Return value
  FrameByID returns the TJvID3Frame component for the specified
  frame. If the frame can not be found, an exception is raised.
See Also
  FindFrame

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.FrameByName
Summary
  Returns a frame given its frame name.
Description
  Call FrameByName to retrieve frame information for a frame when only the frame’s name is known.

  The tag controller uses the TJvID3FrameID type to identify frames. In the tag itself the frames are
  identified by a 4 character long name. Parameter FrameName identifies the frame by the 4 characters.
Note
  FrameByName differs from the FindFrame method only when the named frame is not in the list. When the
  frame is not found, FrameByName raises an exception, while FindFrame returns nil.
Parameters
  FrameName - The frame name of an existing frame.
Return value
  FrameByName returns the TJvID3Frame component for the specified
  frame. If the frame can not be found, an exception is raised.
See Also
  FindFrame

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.Frames
Summary
  Lists the frame references that are managed by the TJvID3Frames object.
Description
  Use Frames to obtain a pointer to a specific frame. The Index parameter indicates the index of the
  frame, where 0 is the index of the first frame, 1 is the index of the second frame, and so on.

  Use Frames with the Count property to iterate through all of the frames in the list.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.Count

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.GetFrameIDs
Summary
  Returns all frame identifiers in the tag.
Description
  Use GetFrameIDs to retrieve all <LINK TJvID3Frame.FrameID,frame identifiers> in the tag.
Return value
  Returns all frame identifiers in the tag as a set of TJvID3FrameID values.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.GetFrameNames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.GetFrameNames
Summary
  Retrieves a list of frame names for all frames in a frames object.
Description
  Call GetFrameNames to fill a list with the frame names for all frames in the frames object.
Parameters

  List - A TStrings descendant that receives the frame names. List must be created and maintained by
         the application.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.FrameByID, TJvID3Frames.FrameByName, TJvID3Frames.Frames, TJvID3Frames.GetFrameIDs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.IndexOf
Summary
  Finds the index of a frame object in the Frames array from the frame object.
Description
  Call IndexOf to get the index for a frame in the Frames array. Specify the frame as the Frame
  parameter.

  The first frame in the array has index 0, the second frame has index 1, and so on. If a frame is
  not in the Frames array, IndexOf returns -1.
Parameters
  Frame - The frame for which to search.
Return value
  Returns the index of the frame object in the Frames array. Returns -1, if the frame is not in the
  Frames array.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.FrameByID, TJvID3Frames.Frames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.Remove
Summary
  Deletes the reference to the Frame parameter from the Frames array.
Description
  Applications do not normally call the Remove method directly. After a frame is removed, all of the
  items that follow it are moved up in index position and the Count is reduced by one.
Note
  Unlike the Clear method, which frees the frame components when it removes them, Remove does not
  free the specified frame component.
Parameters
  Frame - The frame which to delete from the Frames array.
See Also
  TJvID3Frames.Add, TJvID3Frames.Frames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3Frames.RemoveEmptyFrames
Summary
  Removes all empty frames from the Frames array.
Description
  Call RemoveEmptyFrames to remove all empty frames from the Frames array. The <LINK
  TJvID3Frame.IsEmpty,IsEmpty> property of
  a frame indicates whether the frame is empty. For example a text information frame is empty if the
  Text or TextW is set to an empty string.
See Also
  TJvID3Frame.IsEmpty

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
