@@TJvID3NumberFrame
Summary
  Represents a numerical text information frame in a tag.
Description
  Use TJvID3NumberFrame to represent a numerical text information frame in a tag.

  There may only be one text information frame of its kind in a tag.

  The following <LINK TJvID3FrameID,frame identifiers> are supported by TJvID3NumberFrame.

  <TABLE>
  Frame ID, name                  Description
  ----------------------          -----------
  fiBPM -                         The 'BPM' frame contains the number of beats per minute in the main part
   <c>TBPM</c>                     of the audio.
  fiOrigYear -                    The 'Original release year' frame is intended for the year when the original
   <c>TORY</c>                     recording, if for example the music in the file should be a cover of a
                                   previously released song, was released. <b>(Not in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiPlaylistDelay -               The 'Playlist delay' defines the numbers of milliseconds of silence
   <c>TDLY</c>                     that should be inserted before this audio. The value zero indicates
                                   that this is a part of a multifile audio track that should be played continuously.
