@@TJvID3TextFrame
Summary
  Represents a text information frame in a tag.
Description
  The text information frames are the most important frames, containing information like artist,
  album and more. There may only be one text information frame of its kind in a tag.

  Use the Text or TextW property to specify the value of the frame, for example:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  
  <CODE>
 { Sets the value of the Album frame  }
  with TJvID3TextFrame.FindOrCreate(MyTagController, fiAlbum) do
  begin
    Encoding := ienUTF_16;
    TextW := 'The White Album';
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>

  There may only be one text information frame of its kind in a tag.

  The following <LINK TJvID3FrameID,frame identifiers> are supported by TJvID3TextFrame.

  <TABLE>
  Frame ID, name              Description
  -----------------           -----------
  fiAlbum -                   The 'Album/Movie/Show title' frame is intended for the title of the
   <C>TALB</C>                 recording (or source of sound) from which the audio in the file is taken.
  fiAlbumSortOrder -          The 'Album sort order' frame defines a string which should be used
   <C>TSOA</C>                 instead of the album name (fiAlbum) for sorting purposes. E.g. an album
                               named "A Soundtrack" might preferably be sorted as "Soundtrack". <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiBand -                    The 'Band/Orchestra/Accompaniment' frame is used for additional
   <C>TPE2</C>                 information about the performers in the recording.
  fiConductor -               The 'Conductor' frame is used for the name of the conductor.
   <C>TPE3</C>
  fiContentGroup -            The 'Content group description' frame is used if the sound belongs to
   <C>TIT1</C>                 a larger category of sounds/music. For example, classical music is
                               often sorted in different musical sections (e.g. "Piano Concerto",
                               "Weather - Hurricane").
  fiContentType -
   <C>TCON</C>
  fiCopyright -               The 'Copyright message' frame is intended for
   <C>TCOP</C>                 the copyright holder of the original sound, not the audio file itself.
  fiDate -                    The 'Date' frame contains the the date for the recording. <b>(Not in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
   <C>TDAT</C>
  fiEncodedBy -               The 'Encoded by' frame contains the name of the person or
   <C>TENC</C>                 organisation that encoded the audio file.
  fiEncoderSettings -         The 'Software/Hardware and settings used for encoding' frame
   <C>TSSE</C>                 includes the used audio encoder and its settings when the file was
                               encoded. Hardware refers to hardware encoders, not the computer on
                               which a program was run.
  fiFileOwner -               The 'File owner/licensee' frame contains the name of the owner or
   <C>TOWN</C>                 licensee of the file and its contents.
  fiFileType -                The 'File type' frame indicates which type of audio this tag defines.
   <C>TFLT</C>
  fiISRC -                    The 'ISRC' frame should contain the International Standard Recording
   <C>TSRC</C>                 Code (12 characters).
  fiInitialKey -              The 'Initial key' frame contains the musical key in which the sound
   <C>TKEY</C>                 starts.
  fiMediaType -               The 'Media type' frame describes from which media the sound
   <C>TMED</C>                 originated.
  fiMixArtist -               The 'Interpreted, remixed, or otherwise modified by' frame contains
   <C>TPE4</C>                 more information about the people behind a remix and similar
                               interpretations of another existing piece.
  fiMood -                    The 'Mood' frame is intended to reflect the mood of the audio with a
   <C>TMOO</C>                 few keywords, e.g. "Romantic" or "Sad". <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiNetRadioOwner -           The 'Internet radio station owner' frame contains the name of the
   <C>TRSO</C>                 owner of the internet radio station from which the audio is streamed.
  fiNetRadioStation -         The 'Internet radio station name' frame contains the name of the
   <C>TRSN</C>                 internet radio station from which the audio is streamed.
  fiOrigAlbum -               The 'Original album/movie/show title' frame is intended for the title
   <C>TOAL</C>                 of the original recording (or source of sound), if for example the
                               music in the file should be a cover of a previously released song.
  fiOrigFileName -            The 'Original filename' frame contains the preferred filename for the
   <C>TOFN</C>                 file, since some media doesn't allow the desired length of the filename.
  fiPartInSet -               The 'Part of a set' frame is a numeric string that describes which
   <C>TPOS</C>                 part of a set the audio came from. This frame is used if the source described in the fiAlbum
                               frame is divided into several mediums, e.g. a double CD. The value MAY be extended with a "/"
                               character and a numeric string containing the total number of parts in the set. E.g. "1/2".
  fiPerformerSortOrder -      The 'Performer sort order' frame defines a string which should be
   <C>TSOP</C>                 used instead of the performer (TPE2) for sorting purposes. <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiProducedNotice -          The 'Produced notice' frame is intended for the production copyright
   <C>TPRO</C>                 holder of the original sound, not the audio file itself. <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiPublisher -               The 'Publisher' frame simply contains the name of the label or
   <C>TPUB</C>                 publisher.
  fiRecordingDates -          The 'Recording dates' frame contains the recording dates,
   <C>TRDA</C>                 E.g. "4th-7th June, 12th June" in combination with the fiYear frame. <b>(Not in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiSetSubTitle -             The 'Set subtitle' frame is intended for the subtitle of the part of
   <C>TSST</C>                 a set this track belongs to. <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiSubTitle -                The 'Subtitle/Description refinement' frame is used for information
   <C>TIT3</C>                 directly related to the contents title (e.g. "Op. 16" or "Performed
                               live at Wembley").
  fiTime -                    The '\Time' frame contains the time for the recording. <b>(Not in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
   <C>TIME</C>
  fiTitle -                   The 'Title/Songname/Content description' frame is the actual name of the piece
   <C>TIT2</C>                 (e.g. "Adagio", "Hurricane Donna").
  fiTitleSortOrder -          The 'Title sort order' frame defines a string which should be used
   <C>TSOT</C>                 instead of the title (TIT2) for sorting purposes. <b>(Only in v2.4.0 tags)</b>
  fiTrackNum -                The 'Track number/Position in set' frame is a numeric string containing
   <C>TRCK</C>                 the order number of the audio-file on its original recording. This MAY be extended with a "/"
                               character and a numeric string containing the total number of tracks/elements on the original
                               recording. E.g. "4/9".
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvID3NumberFrame, TJvID3TimestampFrame

